 Boston police officer was shot in the face just seconds after approaching a driver who was stopped during a gunfire investigation .
The video shows Angelo West , 41 , immediately jumps out of the car and shoots Officer John Moynihan , 34 , under the eye at close range after the policeman opens the driver-side door .
West then fires at the other officers as he runs across the street .
Boston Police Commissioner William Evans was firing ` under his arm ' at the cops .